quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  67,27,"So when they see it near, the faces of those who did not believe will be grieved and it will be said, “This is what you used to ask for.”"
  67,28,"Say, “Have you considered, Allah can destroy me and those with me or be merciful to us, but who will protect the infidels from the painful punishment?”"
  67,29,"Say, “He is the Beneficent, we believe in Him and put our trust in Him, so you will come to know who it is that is in clear error.”"
  67,30,"Say, “Have you considered, if your water were to go down, then who will bring flowing water?”"
  68,1,Noon. By the pen and that which they write (with it)
  68,2,by the grace of your Fosterer you are not under the influence of the jinn
  68,3,"And there is certainly a reward for you, which will never fail"
  68,4,And you are certainly of an exalted character
  68,5,So you will see and they (too) will see (as to)
  68,6,which of you is afflicted (with madness)
  68,7,Your Fosterer certainly knows best him who has gone astray from His way and He knows best those who receive guidance
  68,8,So do not obey the liars
  68,9,"they like that you should compromise, so that they (too) would compromise"
  68,10,And do not obey any disgraceful person who swears much
  68,11,"defamer, going about spreading slander"
  68,12,"forbidder of good, exceeder of limits, sinful"
  68,13,"merciless, besides that, mean"
  68,14,because he possesses wealth and sons
  68,15,"When Our signs are recited to him, he says, “Stories of the ancient.”"